<subSubSection pageId="214" pageNumber="493" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="214.[179,1385,298,799]" pageId="214" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,874,529,562]" pageId="214" pageNumber="493">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
Woodland Oldfield Mice reportedly live among galleries that naturally 
<taxonomicName box="[665,830,573,602]" form="under" pageId="214" pageNumber="493" rank="form">form under</taxonomicName>
mossy roots, logs, and debris.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="214" pageNumber="493" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="214.[179,1385,298,799]" pageId="214" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[181,532,608,641]" pageId="214" pageNumber="493">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Endangered on The IUCN Red List. The Woodland Oldfield Mouse occurs in less than 5000 km?, which is severely fragmented, and extent and quality of its forest habitat continue to decline.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
